courses.learning_outcomes:
1. To learn Hahn-Banach Theorem;
2. To learn Basic Banach Theory and Hilbert Theory;
3. Bounded Linear Operators.

courses.course_syllabus:
Topics may be chosen amongst:

• Classifications of ordinary differential equations; first order separable equations; homogeneous equations; integrating factor; exact equations;
• Second and higher order linear differential equations with constant coefficients; Wronskians; variations of parameters; reduction of order;
• introduction to existence and uniqueness theory;
• Introduction to non-linear systems and stability theory;
• Power series method, Frobenius’ series method;
• Two-point boundary value problems, Sturm-Liouville problems.

courses.learning_outcomes:
Students are able to understand, and solve, problems using basic knowledge and techniques of elementary probability theory:
• setting up probability models for the problems at hand;
• applying common (discrete or continuous) probability distributions in one- or multi-random variables;
• applying basic theorems and techniques of probability theory.

courses.course_syllabus:
Topics may be chosen amongst:
• Mathematical statements and predicates;
• Basic methods of proofs;
• Basic number theory;
• Basic results in set operations;
• Logic;
• Functions;
• Infinite sets;
• The notion of limits;
• Relations and the number systems.
